Evaluation and choice rationale: The progressive concept record ticks nearly every box from my declared preferences: it is explicitly built as a single‑session listening journey with long, sequenced movements and seamless transitions (matching my taste for records designed to be played straight through), it features shifting time signatures and extended instrumental passages with evolving solos (central to my preference for development and exploration), and it offers cinematic production with wide stereo imaging and consistent, nuanced mastering (which preserves dynamic momentum and spatial depth I prize). Critically, it includes a full remaster, clear metadata and extensive liner notes — exactly the kind of documentation and careful mastering I demand for deep, repeat listens.
